tips.text: One of the Best Bah Kut Teh,imo. I totally love their soup, and side dishes of deepfried doughsticks, peanuts & salted veggies! I've considered this as a gem among my fav foodhunts in town! :)
Make your own bowl! Very colourful and healthy.
Try the Burgers!! A MUST 😍
Have you tried their coffee and toasties? Well, you should.
Must try the salt baked beetroot, w burrata & truffle honey, mini Spanish breakfast, and popcorn milk chocolate mousse! The short ribs and scallops were just okay. Arrive post 930 to avoid the wait.
Been here since I was a kid, gotta try the dai ha mai
Food is totally overpriced but drinks and atmosphere at bar upstairs are great, so have dinner somewhere else and come here only for drinks.
Every single thing we ordered was superb. Reasonably price too
Come up the stairs folks, don't be afraid.

formattedAddress: 2 Teck Lim Road (Off Keong Saik Rd)

tips.text: Good value set lunch. Yummy food with even yummier desserts. Don't miss their lemon tart - One of those rare places that dares to let the tartness shines through. Love!

Pork ears and the spicy oriental bolognaise are must tries.
Duck confit was the best we've had in Singapore. Crispy & fragrant, every bite was pleasurable. And there's that sinful side of potato crisp fried in duck fat. Ahhh...
Bak Kwa! Minced Pork & Sliced Pork are delicious!

My best, love their earl grey lavender & rose raspberry pistachio cakes, & their wonderful matcha green teas. A wifi'd café downstairs, & a flower shoppe upstairs. Super bouquets blooms 4 all seasons.

tips.text: They have the most amazing fried Hokkien mee! Must try! Patronise them and keep the place alive!
Go for the Cheesesteak, it's legit.

Food here is pretty rubbish.  The carbohydrates were overcooked (soba) or cooked horribly (rice).  Meat was dry and soaked in oil.  Vegetables were too oily.  It is definitely not "healthy". 3rd visit
From the folks who brought you Ronin and The Plain; try the drumlets, the fish & chips and the off menu desserts. Just 5 days old but steady showing so much potential. The coffee is also exemplary.

Great for lunch, especially the pork rice! Expect crowd.
Tasty and good value omakase if you don't mind early 6pm seating. Will be back.
Best dining experience - has the potential to be a top 10 restaurant in the world! Chef's 8 course + dessert is full of wonderful surprises, leaving you wanting more!
